HEADWORD: Phenomenalism
<hw>Phe*nom"e*nal*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>That theory which limits positive or
scientific knowledge to phenomena only, whether material or
spiritual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phenomenist</ent>⟦br⟧
